    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-01-14T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-01-14T07:00:00-05:00" n="136"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 296/852: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-01-14T12:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1925—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received January 14—10:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. L–315 [from Herrick, Kellogg and Logan]. Reference Department’s L–196.<note
                        n="31" xml:id="d136fn31">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_142">p. 142</ref>.</note>
                    Subparagraph 2 (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) our L–312 (see our L–312)<note n="32"
                        xml:id="d136fn32">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_140">p. 140</ref>.</note>
                    provides specifically “that the Agreement of May 25, 1923” (in other words
                    specifically the Wadsworth Agreement) “does not apply to payments on account of
                    reparation by any ex-enemy powers other than Germany”. Will be seen by this that
                    only waiver we have made is waiver under Wadsworth Agreement for claims such as
                    example the Bulgarian moneys<note n="33" xml:id="d136fn33">For previous
                        correspondence concerning Bulgarian payments, see <ref
                            target="frus1924v02#pg_152">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1924, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp. 152</ref> ff.</note> and in no way
                    affects the rights we have under our treaties with Austria, Hungary and Turkey.
                    Herrick, Kellogg, Logan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
